process.name: Utility - Blue Prism Process Info
process.narrative:
A utility object for retrieving basic information about processes defined in the Blue Prism environment.
Version: 2.6

condition.narrative: This object requires the Blue Prism SQL Server utility object.

stage.name: Get Processes
stage.narrative: Method for getting the names and descriptions of all processes defined in the Bue Prism system.

condition.narrative: A successful call to the 'Set Connection Details' method.

input.name: Include Objects
input.narrative: Flag indicating whether objects should be included in the set of results. If True, objects will be included. Default value: False

output.name: Success
output.narrative: A flag indicating the success or failure of the method.

output.name: Processes
output.narrative: A collection of names and descriptions for all processes defined in the Blue Prism system.

stage.name: Note1
stage.narrative:
Clean Up Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.
The cleanup action will be called automatically immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.

stage.name: Note2
stage.narrative:
Initialise Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.
The initialise action will be called automatically immediately after loading your business object.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.

stage.name: Set Connection Details
stage.narrative: Use this method to set the database hostname, database name, and user credentials for connecting to the Blue Prism database.

input.name: Database Server
input.narrative: The hostname and SQL instance of the Blue Prism SQL Server (ex.LOCALHOST\SQLEXPRESS).

input.name: Database Name
input.narrative: The name of the Blue Prism database within the SQL Server instance.

input.name: Database Credential Name
input.narrative: The name of the user credential defined in Credential Manager with access rights on the Blue Prism database.

output.name: Success
output.narrative: Flag indicating success or failure of the method.

input.name: Raise exception on any failure
input.narrative: Flag indicating if failure should cause an exception to be raised rather than a return of a success output value

input.name: Server
input.narrative: The name of the server and, if necessary, instance name of the SQL Server instance to connect to

input.name: Database
input.narrative: The name of the database to connect to

input.name: User
input.narrative: If appropriate, the login name to use to connect to SQL Server. If left empty, windows authentication using the current user will be used instead of SQL Server authentication

input.name: Password
input.narrative: If appropriate, the password to use with the above login name to access SQL Server. Unused for windows authentication

Get the specified set of credentials.
An Exception will occur if access to the credentials is not allowed, based on the running Resource, Process and User.

output.name: Password
output.narrative: The password

output.name: Username
output.narrative: The user name

output.name: Expiry Date
output.narrative: The expiry date

output.name: Status
output.narrative: The status

stage.name: Query
stage.initialvalue: SELECT [name] AS Process_Name, [description] AS Process_Description, [AttributeID] AS Attribute_ID, [wspublishname] AS WS_Name, CASE WHEN [ProcessType] = 'P' THEN 'Process' ELSE 'Object' END AS Type FROM [dbo].[BPAProcess] WHERE [ProcessType]='P'

input.name: SQL
input.narrative: The SQL query to use to perform this action

output.name: Success
output.narrative: Flag indicating success (True) or failure (False)

output.name: Message
output.narrative: Error message giving detail regarding why this action failed

output.name: Results
output.narrative: The collection of results from the query

calculation.expression: "The following exception was encountered while trying to get the process names: " & ExceptionDetail()

stage.name: Note3
stage.narrative: NOTE: This method is NOT intended to be exposed. It is only for internal use within this VBO.

field.name: Description
field.description: An optional description of the process.

field.name: Published_WS
field.description: Flag indicating whether the process has been published as a SOAP web service.

field.name: WS_Name
field.description: If published, the web service name of the process.

field.name: Published_ControlRoom
field.description: Flag indicating whether the process has been published in the Blue Prism Control Room.

field.name: Type
field.description: The type of entity (either Process or Object)

input.name: Collection Name
input.narrative: The name of the collection to act upon

field.name: Type
field.description: The data type of the parameter.

field.name: Direction
field.description: A string indicating whether the parameter is an INPUT or OUTPUT parameter.

input.narrative: The XML-encoded process definition.

output.name: Parameters
output.narrative: Collection containing any Input/Output parameters defined on the processes Main page.

stage.name: Get Session Output
stage.narrative: Use this method to get the output from a specific session of a Blue Prism process.

condition.narrative: You must provide a valid session ID for a completed Blue Prism process.

stage.name: Query
stage.initialvalue: SELECT [b].[attributexml] FROM [dbo].[BPASession] AS a JOIN [dbo].[BPASessionLog_NonUnicode] AS b ON [a].[sessionnumber] = [b].[sessionnumber] WHERE [b].[stagename]='End' AND [a].[sessionid]=

output.name: Success
output.narrative: A flag indicating the success or failure of the method.

output.name: Session Output
output.narrative: An XML encoded string containing the output of the session.

input.name: SQL
input.narrative: The SQL query to use to perform this action

output.name: Success
output.narrative: Flag indicating success (True) or failure (False)

output.name: Message
output.narrative: Error message giving detail regarding why this action failed

output.name: Results
output.narrative: The collection of results from the query

calculation.expression: "The following exception was encountered while trying to retrieve process results from the database for session '" & [SessionID] & "': " & ExceptionDetail()

stage.name: Parse Output XML
stage.narrative: Strip extraneous element tags from the output XML.

stage.name: Note5
stage.narrative:
If a process has multiple pages in it and any of those pages End stage has output values, the query we run to collect output will return all of them. We want to limit our response to just the output from the very last End stage which should be that of the Main page.
To do that, we cycle through the collection, basically throwing away everything except the very last entry. Keep in mind, there could be cases where a process has sub pages that return output internally within the process, but the Main page does not. In that case, we don't return anything.
